<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Physics Career Roadmap</title>
<style>
body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
  background: #0f172a;
  color: white;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.slide {
  width: 100vw;
  height: 100vh;
  display: none;
  padding: 60px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.active {
  display: block;
}

h1 {
  font-size: 48px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 32px;
  margin-bottom: 15px;
  color: #38bdf8;
}

.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 30px;
}

.card {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
  padding: 20px;
  border-radius: 15px;
  box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
}

img {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 10px;
}

.nav {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 20px;
  right: 20px;
}

button {
  padding: 10px 15px;
  margin: 5px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 8px;
  background: #38bdf8;
  color: black;
  cursor: pointer;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<!-- Slide 1 -->
<div class="slide active">
  <h1>From Classroom to Career</h1>
  <h2>Physics Roadmap (Class 11–12)</h2>
  <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400">
</div>

<!-- Slide 2 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>The Reality</h1>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>Students study Physics for exams, not for careers.</p>
      <p>Massive skill gap exists in India.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x300">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 3 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>Class 11 Physics</h1>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Mechanics Core</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Units & Measurements</li>
        <li>Kinematics</li>
        <li>Laws of Motion</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Energy & Systems</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Work, Energy, Power</li>
        <li>Rotational Motion</li>
        <li>Gravitation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 4 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>Advanced Concepts</h1>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Thermal Physics</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Thermodynamics</li>
        <li>Kinetic Theory</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Waves</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Oscillations</li>
        <li>Wave Motion</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 5 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>Class 12 Physics</h1>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Electricity & Magnetism</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Electrostatics</li>
        <li>Current Electricity</li>
        <li>Magnetism</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Modern Physics</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Dual Nature</li>
        <li>Atoms & Nuclei</li>
        <li>Semiconductors</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 6 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>Practical Skills</h1>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Experiments</h2>
      <p>Vernier Calipers, Pendulum, Friction, Circuits</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Real Skills</h2>
      <p>Problem solving, observation, data analysis</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 7 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>The Problem</h1>
  <p>Even after all this… students don’t know where Physics leads.</p>
</div>

<!-- Slide 8 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>The Shift You Need</h1>
  <ul>
    <li>Study for careers, not exams</li>
    <li>Map every chapter → real-world application</li>
    <li>Build skills alongside concepts</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- Slide 9 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>What I Will Teach You</h1>
  <ul>
    <li>Physics → Career Mapping</li>
    <li>Conceptual clarity</li>
    <li>Real-world applications</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- Slide 10 -->
<div class="slide">
  <h1>Welcome to the Journey 🚀</h1>
</div>

<div class="nav">
  <button onclick="prev()">Prev</button>
  <button onclick="next()">Next</button>
</div>

<script>
let slides = document.querySelectorAll(".slide");
let index = 0;

function showSlide(i){
  slides.forEach(s => s.classList.remove("active"));
  slides[i].classList.add("active");
}

function next(){
  if(index < slides.length - 1){
    index++;
    showSlide(index);
  }
}

function prev(){
  if(index > 0){
    index--;
    showSlide(index);
  }
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
